  "texts": [
    "Soft voting is a technique used in ensemble learning where the final class is determined based on the probability predictions from multiple models.",
    "Instead of each model voting for a single class (hard voting), in soft voting, each model's vote is weighted by its confidence in each class.",
    "The final prediction is the class with the highest total scores across all models.",
    "This method often results in better performance since it considers the uncertainty of the model's predictions.",
    "The effectiveness of this approach is demonstrated through its high agreement with human expert re-identifications, offering a promising tool for assessing and resolving identification inconsistencies."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}